@startuml SCRUM-48 Buyer Search Items

title Buyer Search Items by Name (SCRUM-48)

actor Buyer as U
participant "Browser\n(home-navbar / search.jsp)" as B
participant "SecurityFilter\n/*" as SF
participant "SearchServlet\nGET /search" as S
participant "InputValidator\n+ SecurityUtil" as V
participant "SearchDAO" as DAO
database "PostgreSQL\n(auction + auction_details)" as DB

== User submits search ==

U -> B : Type keyword in search bar → submit
B -> SF : GET /search?q=keyword&page=1&size=12
note right of SF
  SecurityFilter (/*) adds
  security headers only — no auth.
  /search is PUBLIC (SCRUM-260 decision):
  buyers do not need to log in to search.
end note
activate SF
SF -> S : chain
deactivate SF

activate S

== SCRUM-294: Validate + sanitize query ==

S -> S : read q, page, size params
S -> V : getSearchQueryViolation(q)

alt q blank
    S -> B : Redirect / (home)
else q too long (> 200 chars)
    S -> B : req attr "searchError" + forward search.jsp\n(error banner shown, no DB call)
else q valid
    V --> S : null (valid)
    note right of S
      <b>SCRUM-294</b>: q is bound as PreparedStatement
      parameter — no string concatenation.
      Pattern built as: '%' + q + '%'
      Sanitized copy (SecurityUtil.sanitize)
      used only when echoed in JSP/logs.
    end note
    S -> S : clamp page ≥ 1; clamp size 1–50
end

== SCRUM-258: DAO query (ILIKE, pagination) ==

S -> DAO : search(keyword, page, size)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB : SELECT a.auction_id, d.title, d.category,\n  COALESCE(max_bid, d.starting_price) AS current_price,\n  a.date_end, u.username, thumbnail\nFROM auction a\nJOIN auction_details d ON d.id = a.auction_id\nJOIN users u ON u.id = a.seller_id\nWHERE a.moderation_state = 'active'\n  AND a.date_end > CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\n  AND (d.title ILIKE ? OR d.description ILIKE ?)\nORDER BY a.date_created DESC\nLIMIT ? OFFSET ?
note right of DB
  <b>SCRUM-258</b>: ILIKE = case-insensitive
  (SCRUM-259 case policy).
  <b>SCRUM-261</b>: Parameters bound via
  PreparedStatement — SQL injection
  impossible regardless of keyword chars.
  LIMIT/OFFSET = pagination.
end note
DB --> DAO : result rows
DAO --> S : List<SearchResultItem>
deactivate DAO

S -> DAO : count(keyword)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB : SELECT COUNT(*) …same WHERE…
DB --> DAO : total
DAO --> S : int total
deactivate DAO

S -> S : totalPages = ceil(total / size)
S -> S : sanitizedQuery = SecurityUtil.sanitize(keyword)\n(for echo in JSP — SCRUM-294)

== SCRUM-259: Empty results UX ==

alt results empty
    note right of S
      req attr "searchEmpty" = true
      JSP renders "No results found for '…'"
    end note
end

S -> B : forward search.jsp\n(results, total, currentPage, totalPages, sanitizedQuery)
deactivate S

== JSP renders results ==

B -> U : Search results page\n(card grid + pagination + result count)

note over U, DB
  <b>SCRUM-259</b>: empty → friendly "No results" banner.
  <b>SCRUM-260</b>: Auth policy = PUBLIC. No session required.
  <b>SCRUM-294</b>: sanitizedQuery echoed via <c:out> (HTML-escaped).
end note

@enduml
